The National Drugs Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) yesterday brought a businessman, Ezekiel Ibe, before the Federal High Court, Lagos for allegedly being in possession of  5,458. 894 kilogrammes of Tramadol, without lawful authority. It said Ibe, 48, was arrested with the banned drugs on December 23, 2021, at Amuwo-Odofin, Lagos. Prosecution counsel Jerry Aernan told the court that the alleged offence contravened section 11(c) of the NDLEA Act, 2004. The charge against the defendant reads: “That you Ezekiel Ibe, male, adult, 48 years old, on or about the 23rd day of December 2021, at Amuwo-Odofin, Lagos State, without lawful authority knowingly possessed 5,458. 894 kgs of Tramadol psychotropic substance similar to cocaine, heroin and LSD…”   2023: Vote for trusted leaders, says clergy     Accord Party working with external bodies to win…     Yiaga Africa trains 74 legislative aides   The defendant pleaded not guilty. - Advertisement - His counsel, Maxwell Okpara, informed the court that he had filed his client’s bail application, adding that the defendant had health challenges that could not be handled at the Nigerian Correctional Service (NCoS). He was opposed by the prosecutor, on the ground that there was neither any affidavit nor medical report indicating his health challenge But in a bench ruling, Justice Yellim Bogoro granted the defendant bail in the sum of N10 million with two sureties. He adjourned till April 7 and May 9, for trial.   SPONSORED